JOHANNESBURG - The country s banks have expressed their willingness to work with new Finance Minister Malusi Gigaba.READ: I m not trying to fill anybody s shoes: GigabaThe Banking Association of South Africa met with the minister and his deputy on Wednesday.The association team included the CEOs of Standard Bank, Absa, Nedbank, First Rand and Investec.The CEO of Deutsche Bank represented locally-based international banks.In a statement, the association said government assured it, there would be no shift in policy.READ: I will not betray our people, says GigabaThe parties agreed there's a need to address the ratings downgrade and improve the economy.*For more on this story, watch the full video report by Malungelo Booi in the gallery above.eNCA